cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

The paper proposes a computational model for human reading behavior using neural attention and autoencoding, which falls under the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on eye-tracking data, which is commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision research. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI due to the use of neural networks and reinforcement learning in the proposed model. Finally, cs.NE is also a likely sub-category due to the focus on attention mechanisms in the model.
